==English==

===Noun===
'''truthiness''' (1)

# the quality by which one is convinced of a belief, to the neglect of observable facts or of rational thought
# the quality of adhering to concepts one wishes or believes to be true, rather than the facts

'''truthiness''' (2)

# variation of ''truthfulness'', ''faithfulness'', derivational morpheme of "truthy"; archaic and rare or dialectal [http://itre.cis.upenn.edu/~myl/languagelog/archives/002586.html]

==Origination==

An episode of the popular television show, "The Colbert Report"